properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 11 at 11:16AM CST until January 12 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Chicago IL
properties.description:
...Periods of Wintry Precipitation Today and Accumulating Snow
Late this Afternoon and this Evening...

* WHAT...Periodic rain is likely to change over to a wintry mix,
mainly light but potentially including ice, from north to
south across the county this morning and early afternoon.
Total ice accumulations of up to one tenth of an inch are
possible, with some light sleet accumulation also possible. A
transition to snow, possibly briefly heavy, is expected late
this afternoon or early this evening. Total snow accumulations
of 3 to 6 inches are forecast. Northeast winds will gust as
high as 50 mph near the lake and 40 to 45 mph inland. These
winds combined with the winter precipitation may cause further
impacts, especially reduced visibility in snow late this
afternoon and evening.

* WHERE...Lake IL County.

* WHEN...Through 3 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could become impacted at times today and
tonight, especially in the snow late this afternoon and this
evening. Patchy blowing snow could significantly reduce
visibility later this afternoon and tonight.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for Illinois can be obtained on the
internet at www.gettingaroundillinois.com.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM CST SUNDAY
